7. Mathematical Definition of RIS

Let:
	â€¢	F_i be binary fallacy detectors
	â€¢	C be the causal integrity test
	â€¢	L be the logical structure validity
	â€¢	S be structural soundness

Then:

RIS = w_L L + w_C C + w_S S - \sum_i w_{F_i} F_i

Where:
	â€¢	w_L + w_C + w_S = 1
	â€¢	w_L, w_C, w_S > 0
	â€¢	w_{F_i} \ge 0

Pass threshold:

RIS \ge \tau_{hyp}

Default:
\tau_{hyp} = 0.75

